The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, May 17: Siemens will split equity shares of the company in the ratio of 1:5. The shareholders have approved splitting of equity shares of the company of Rs 10 into five equity shares of the face value of Rs 2 each. The company?s shares closed at Rs 5,914.90, up 3.11 per cent on the BSE. 

 Mumbai, May 17: The government today appointed P.L. Gairola as chairman and managing director of Dena Bank. Gairola, who took over charge as CMD today, earlier served as executive director of the Bank of India. 

 New Delhi, May 17: Public sector oil retailing firms are losing $51 million daily on selling fuel below cost, petroleum secretary M.S. Srinivasan said today. ?The daily loss to oil marketing companies is $51 million. This came down today as a result of a fall in crude prices to $50.91 million,? he said.

 Mumbai, May 17: Fedders Lloyd Corporation will raise Rs 300 crore through the issue of global depository receipts, foreign currency convertible bonds or other securities in the international markets. 

 Mumbai, May 17: Max India will allot 10.68 lakh equity shares to the promoters. The board today approved the allotment of 4.68 lakh shares of Rs 10 each for Rs 200 each to Liquid Investment and Trading Company, a part of its promoter group.




